t: "O believers! Let those Ë¹bondspeopleËº in your possession and those of you who are still under age ask for your permission Ë¹to come inËº at three times: before dawn prayer, when you take off your Ë¹outerËº clothes at noon, and after the late evening prayer. Ë¹These areËº three times of privacy for you. Other than these times, there is no blame on you or them to move freely, attending to one another. This is how God makes the revelations clear to you, for God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"